modules.description: This module handles network communication for IRC clients using Unix sockets. It provides functions to connect to IRC servers via IPv4 or IPv6, send and receive raw IRC messages, and manage socket input/output streams. Concrete use cases include establishing a connection to an IRC server, reading incoming messages in real-time, and sending user commands like JOIN or PRIVMSG over the network.

This module implements IRC client functionality using Unix sockets for network communication. It provides functions to connect to IRC servers, send and receive IRC messages like JOIN, PRIVMSG, and PONG, and maintain persistent connections with automatic reconnection. Concrete use cases include building IRC bots that join channels, respond to messages, or handle server pings.
